    <main class="savings-page">
      <div class="savings-title">
        <h2>Saving Tips</h2>
        <p>
          Simple ways to reduce electricity and water usage at home.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="savings-content">
        <div class="resource-card">
          <div class="resource-card-body">
            <h4>Did You Know?</h4>
            <p>
              Small habits such as turning off lights and taking shorter showers can help reduce household bills over time.
            </p>
            <p>
              Did you know? A leaking tap can waste more than 20,000 litres of water each year.
            </p>
            <p>
              Did you know? Leaving a tap running for just one minute can use up to 9 litres of water.
            </p>
            <p>
              Did you know? LED light bulbs use less electricity than traditional bulbs.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="savings-flex">
          <div class="resource-card">
            <div class="resource-card-body">
              <h4>Energy Saving Tips</h4>
              <details>
               <summary>Use LED Light Bulbs</summary>
               <p>
                  LED bulbs use less electricity and last longer than traditional bulbs.
               </p>
              </details>
              <details>
               <summary>Turn Off Unused Devices</summary>
               <p>
                 Turn off lights, fans, and electronics when they are not being used.
               </p>
              </details>
              <details>
               <summary>Use Natural Lighting</summary>
                <p>
                  Open curtains during the day instead of using lights whenever possible.
               </p>
             </details>
            </div>
          </div>
         <div class="resource-card">
           <div class="resource-card-body">
              <h4>Water saving tips</h4>
             <details>
               <summary>Take shorter showers</summary>
               <p>
                  Reducing shower time can help save a large amount of water every week.
               </p>
             </details>
              <details>
               <summary>Fix Leaking Taps</summary>
                <p>
                 Check for leaking taps in your home, small leaks can waste a lot of water over time if not repaired.
               </p>
             </details>
              <details>
               <summary>Turn Off the water</summary>
               <p>
                  Turning the tap off while brushing your teeth and while you are shampooing or washing your body helps reduce unnecessary water usage.
               </p>
             </details>
            </div>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="resource-card">
          <div class="resource-card-body">
            <h4>Family and Kids Tips</h4>
            <details>
              <summary>Light Reminder Notes</summary>
              <p>
                Place reminder notes near switches to help children remember to turn lights off.
              </p>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary>Family Saving Challenge</summary>
              <p>
                Create a weekly challenge to encourage shorter showers and reduced electricity usage.
              </p>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary>Make Saving Easy to Understand</summary>
              <p>
                Explain to children why saving water and electricity is important using simple examples.
              </p>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="resource-card">
          <div class="resource-card-body">
            <h4>Common Mistakes</h4>
            <details>
              <summary>Leaving Chargers Plugged In</summary>
              <p>
                Chargers can still use electricity even when not charging a device.
              </p>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary>Using the Dryer Too Often</summary>
              <p>
                Clothes dryers use a large amount of electricity. A clothesline can help save money.
              </p>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary>Half-Full Washing Loads</summary>
              <p>
                Washing small loads wastes both water and electricity. So try to wash full loads.
              </p>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="resource-card">
          <div class="resource-card-body">
            <h4>Appliance Cost Examples</h4>
            <table>
              <tr>
                <th>Appliance</th>
                <th>Usage</th>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Air Conditioner</td>
                <td>High</td>
                <td>Use fans more often</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Clothes Dryer</td>
                <td>High</td>
                <td>Use clothesline or drying rack more often and only use clothes dryer if neccessary</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
               <td>Heater</td>
                <td>High</td>
                <td>Use warm clothing before turning heaters on.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Washing Machine</td>
                <td>Medium</td>
                <td>Wash full loads using cold water.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Television</td>
                <td>Medium</td>
                <td>Turn it off when nobody is watching.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>LED Light</td>
                <td>Low</td>
                <td>Replace the bulbs with LED light bulbs.
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Phone Charger</td>
                <td>Low</td>
                <td>Unplug chargers when not charging devices.</td>
              </tr>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="resource-card">
          <div class="resource-card-body">
            <h4>Daily Habit Reminders</h4>
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" />
              Turn off lights before leaving a room
            </label>
            <br /><br />
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" />
              Take shorter showers
            </label>
            <br /><br />
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" />
              Unplug chargers when not in use
            </label>
            <br /><br />
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" />
              Use cold water for washing clothes
            </label>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
